HEADWORD: Protohippus
<hw>Pro`to*hip"pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/ first + <?/ horse.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of
fossil horses from the Lower Pliocene. They had three toes on each foot,
the lateral ones being small.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

